pr_title: Auto delete workers on challenge unapproval.
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 459214461, 'comment_body': '@KhalidRmb What is this condition checking? Can you please mention in the comment?

What if I have 5 workers for a challenge running and I unapproved a challenge.
- Would all the 5 workers will be deleted?
- Do I need to manually reduce them to 1 and then unapprove the challenge?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 23, 4, 57, 10, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RishabhJain2018', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 459418158, 'comment_body': '@RishabhJain2018 It basically checks that the number of successful deletions is same as the number of challenges in the array passed to delete_workers.

Yes, all 5 workers will be deleted. (The implementation is that the workers will be scaled down to 0 as is required by AWS, and then the service is deleted.)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 23, 12, 41, 11, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'KhalidRmb', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 459528182, 'comment_body': 'okay, can you please add it as comment.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 23, 15, 16, 39, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'RishabhJain2018', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: Add backend to support uploading large files.
pr_body:
Adds APIs and util methods to enable generation of a presigned url and enable the pipeline to upload large annotation files and submission files through CLI.

Related: https://github.com/Cloud-CV/evalai-cli/pull/277

pr_body: This PR includes the backend changes to enable GitHub based challenges. Changes: - Refactor Abstract out and make relevant changes to Challenge config validation API - Add new API for GitHub challenges MVP - The above API handled both updates and creation for a Github based challenge, and is called from the build step in the host's private repository through Github Actions - Add a field in Challenge model for storing the github_repository identifier which uniquely identifies a private github repository (of the format: /) - Changes in tests and serialisers to incorporate the changes in the Challenge model

@RishabhJain2018 @deshraj @Ram81
